At the tail end of an illuminating year for their global credentials, Dutch newcomers Blasterjaxx make a loud and proud return to Revealed Recordings with latest solo installment "Mystica." Back on the trail after unleashing his debut smash "Fifteen," yet another of the exclusive IDs from Hardwell's Tomorrowworld set is given a formal introduction to global club land. The duo's signature electro sound dominates the track from start to finish, using intricate leads and powerful peak time energy to score yet another fine notch in the label's output for 2013. In further testament to the focus on new age talent embraced by Revealed of late, "Mystica" asserts Blasterjaxx as promising contenders to throne for the year.
